      <hr><a name="skip_menu"></a><h1>072 - Subject Category Code (R)</h1>
      <hr>
      <div class="formatname">MARC 21 Bibliographic - Full</div>
      <div class="datename">October 2003</div>
      <hr>
      <table width="100%">
         <tr vAlign="top">
            <td width="45%"><strong>First Indicator</strong><br><em>Undefined</em><br># - Undefined <br><br></td>
            <td width="45%"><strong>Second Indicator</strong><br><em>Code source</em><br>0 - NAL subject category code list <br>7 - Source specified in subfield $2 <br><br></td>
         </tr>
      </table>
      <hr>
      <table width="100%">
         <tr vAlign="top">
            <td valign="top" width="50%" align="left"></td>
            <td valign="top" width="50%" align="left"></td>
         </tr>
         <tr vAlign="top">
            <td colspan="2"><strong>Subfield Codes</strong><br></td>
         </tr>
         <tr vAlign="top">
            <td colspan="1">$a - Subject category code (NR) <br>$x - Subject category code subdivision (R)<br>$2 - Source (NR)<br></td>
            <td colspan="1">$6 - Linkage (NR) <br>$8 - Field link and sequence number (R) <br></td>
         </tr>
   </table>
      <hr>
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <p>Code for the subject category that is associated with the described item.</p>
      <p>Repeated for multiple subject category codes.</p>
      <hr>
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> INDICATORS
      </h4>
      <div class="indicator"><strong>First Indicator - Undefined</strong> <div class="description">Undefined and contains a blank (#).
            </div>
      </div>
      <div class="indicator"><strong>Second Indicator - Code source</strong> <div class="description">Source of the subject category code.
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong>0 - NAL subject category code list</strong> <div class="description">Source of the subject category code is <em>AGRICOLA Subject Category Codes with
                                             Scope Notes</em>.
                  <div class="example">
                     <table width="100%">
                        <tr>
                           <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                           <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>072</strong></td>
                           <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>#0</strong><strong>$a</strong>K800
                           </td>
                        </tr>
                     </table>
                  </div>
               </div>
            </div>
            <div class="indicatorvalue"><strong>7 - Source specified in subfield $2</strong> </div>
         </div>
      </div>
      <h4><span class="box">&#9632;</span> SUBFIELD CODES
      </h4>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$a - Subject category code</strong> <div class="description">Code for the broad subject associated with the item.</div>
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>072</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>#0</strong><strong>$a</strong>F821
                  </td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>072</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>#0</strong><strong>$a</strong>J500
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$x - Subject category code subdivision</strong> <div class="description">Level of specificity within the broader category coded in subfield
                           $a.
         </div>
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>072</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>#7</strong><strong>$a</strong>Z1<strong>$x</strong>.630<strong>$2</strong>mesh
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$2 - Source</strong> <div class="description">MARC code that identifies the thesaurus used to assign the subject category code
                              when the second indicator position contains value 7.  Code from: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/standards/sourcelist/subject-category.html">Subject Category Code Source Codes</a></em>.
         </div>
         <div class="example">
            <table width="100%">
               <tr>
                  <td valign="top" width="5%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="10%" align="left"></td>
                  <td valign="top" width="15%" align="left"></td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>072</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>#7</strong><strong>$a</strong>17<strong>$x</strong>02.1<strong>$2</strong>cosatisc
                  </td>
               </tr>
               <tr>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="1" align="left"><strong>072</strong></td>
                  <td vAlign="top" colspan="9" align="left"><strong>#7</strong><strong>$a</strong>B<strong>$2</strong>lcmd
                  </td>
               </tr>
            </table>
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$6 - Linkage</strong> <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="subfield"><strong>$8 - Field link and sequence number</strong> <div class="description">See description of this subfield in Appendix A: <em><a href="http://www.loc.gov/marc/bibliographic/ecbdcntf.html">Control
                                       Subfields</a></em>.
         </div>
      </div>
      <hr>
      <h3>CONTENT DESIGNATOR HISTORY</h3>
      <div class="font_small"><em>Indicator 2 - Code source (BK, SE) [NEW, 1981]</em><br>Definition of the second indicator position in 1981 broadened the scope of this field
                        to include codes taken from any subject category codes list. Prior to that time, the
                        field was used only for <em>AGRICOLA Subject Category Codes</em> and the second
                        indicator contained a # meaning undefined.
      </div>
